## 📊 Detailed Component Analysis

### Frontend (Next.js 16.2.1)
**Strengths:**
- Modern stack: Next.js 16, React 19.2, Tailwind v4
- Standalone output for containerization
- Redux Toolkit for state management
- Stripe React SDK integration

**Concerns:**
- No test files found
- No error boundary components visible
- No Sentry or error tracking integration
- No performance monitoring (Core Web Vitals)

### Core Backend (NestJS 11)
**Strengths:**
- Comprehensive security middleware (session, CSRF, passport)
- Good separation of concerns (modules for auth, billing, payments)
- Raw SQL with pg driver for performance
- Automatic SQL migrations
- Throttler for rate limiting (though too aggressive)

**Concerns:**
- No health check beyond basic `GET /`
- No metrics exposure (Prometheus)
- No graceful shutdown handling visible
- No circuit breaker for Stripe API failures

### Webhooks Backend (NestJS 11)
**Strengths:**
- Proper raw body handling for Stripe signatures
- Idempotent event processing
- Comprehensive event type handling
- Email notifications via Resend

**Concerns:**
- NO rate limiting
- Minimal exception filtering (only global filter)
- No webhook event replay mechanism for failed events
- No queue/buffer for high webhook volume

### Database Layer
**Strengths:**
- Transaction support
- Migration system
- Connection pooling via pg Pool
- UUID primary keys
- Proper indexing

**Concerns:**
- No connection retry logic visible in queries
- No query timeout configurations
- No slow query logging
- Missing ON DELETE CASCADE review (verify intentional)

